EJIKEME OMENAZU/ OYENIRAN APATA LAGOS – Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu of Lagos State on Monday pledged commitment to improved welfare and security of the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) members serving in the state. Sanwo-Olu spoke as 1,832 Batch C, Stream 11 fresh corps members comprising 1,286 females and 546 males, posted to Lagos took oath of allegiance to mark the commencement of their service year. Sanwo-Olu, who was represented by Dr. Yusuf Jimoh, Permanent Secretary, Ministry of Special Duties and Intergovernmental Affairs, stressed that the NYSC scheme was established by its founding fathers for the dual purpose of serving as a platform to drive national integration, as well as to harness and mobilise the creative and productive energies of the youths for national development. He maintained that over the years, the objectives of the scheme had been vigorously and successfully implemented, adding that thousands of youths had been mobilised under the scheme, who had contributed immensely to the growth and development of the country. “Besides promoting national unity and integration, the NYSC scheme has become an important tool for the implementation of critical national development programmes,” he stressed, describing the orientation programme as a very critical aspect of the service as it had been providing the platform to prepare the participants for the challenges and opportunities of the service year and beyond…